Gets hard around lvl 120. Definitely hard at 130. Crashes if you walk backwards while shooting a high quantity ammo gun at a hoard, especially with double tap. Processing just can't support it, but working around it adds a new dimension to the gameplay. Learn to walk forward or just STAND STILL while shooting at a hoard to stop crashing the app. To get to high levels legitly you should pop everything's head using MINIMAL ammo (increasing chance of drop, also gives more points) then get every zombie into your screen and shoot all with the thunder gun or Zeus cannon. You WILL get a drop... often 2 or 3. They all have to be in the screen though. I've gotten 5+ drops per level as each level has multiple waves. Don't die from your own grenades like a doofus and be sure to use monkeys to focus them for 2x points drops. I'm at level 134 right now with about 750,000 points and still only spend a few minutes clearing each level. Legit! The difficulty only got interesting about level 120. Gameplay is very similar to the console version but stays easy far longer. Dogs appear more frequently at high levels, and the quantity of them increases as well. Good luck....  Oh yeah.... If you actually want to go back in time if you die and revive, it is possible via crashing the game with walking backwards while shooting a hoard with lots of ammo once you revive. Just be sure not to go to the next level. You will be able to reopen the game at the previous save point. But that's not legit, is it.

THIS GAME IS TRASH.  The multi-player section is useless,  if you read through the comments not one person was able to connect to a single online game. It's basically false advertising.   Single player on the other hand does work properly.  However, because a mobile version of this game has been created many "easter eggs" have been removed.    Pros & Cons  Pro: Zombies don't seem to trap you as easily. walking into them pushes them aside making it easy to train in smaller areas or walking past them in narrow areas such as stairways.   Cons: Multi-player is a game mode that will absolutely NOT WORK.  Many attempts to fix this have been made by users who have the ability to play with the settings on their Wi-Fi router.  So unless your a computer tech genius. Multi-player is not for you.   Cons: The fact that we have to pay $5 or whatever for the initial purchase of this game should be enough to enjoy it without being forced to purchase every single wall Weapon/ Turrets/ Traps with coins.  ( Coins are acquired with Real Currency)  It's a game you have to dump additional Real Currency into just to unlock the map completly.  By the time you unlock everything using Real Currency you might just save yourself some money buy purchasing the actual Console or PC Game which has a way better user interface and graphics.   Cons:  -The secret songs hidden on each map can be activated but no actual music will play.   - Training properly can only be achieved by increasing your X-Axis sensitivity all the way up.    - I can't speak for others on this one but I was unable to crouch at all,  which poses a problem on certain maps like ascension with the spinning machine in the staring room  Rating: Honestly I regret wasting the space on my phone for this game. Highly disappointed.

I was super hyped after I found this game in the mobile store, however, the game is in need of some trouble shooting and polishing.   You should review the controls, or give us a choice as to where the controls in the game can be placed. For example, I have tiny thumbs, so I constantly have to stop moving all together in order to knife a zombie or do an action. I want to be able to sprint by the mystery box and activate it while fleeing from a hoard of zombies while dodging a zombie coming right at me, but I can't because I can't reach the action buttons. The result? I die.   Combined with the stilled joy sticks option, you should add a function in the "controls menu" that would allow us (the player) to manually drag the control buttons (action button, reload, knife, switch guns, etc.) Into places on the screen for easier access.  Another example, I cannot reach the action button while still in motion. The "button placement," would allow me to drag the "button" to a place that would provide me easier access.    Other than all of that, the game is pretty dang great, you just need to polish it a bit.

This game is so much fun, and this is my 3rd time buying it, because I keep breaking my tablet, but I have Ben a big fan of zombies for sends I was 4 or 3 when waw came out. If you are a big fan of zombies I really recommend this to you. My only complaint is that it is hard to play with poeple unless you are doing local wifi then it is easy to play with someone as long as they are in your house or using the same wifi as you. The game has most of the weapons and there are enough maps to keep me occupied for a while. There is dead ops arcade which has a cool way of unlocking. There is kino. There is fivd, and there is accentoin. My favorite. Last but not least there is call of the dead on there which is a challenge. You can save your progress in the game as well if you are in a high round. I do wish you could have more than one save thoe. Also if you have a slow tablet or phone you can add fog or something to make the game run faster. There are lots of controls to fit your play style, and over all this is one of the best mobile games I think I may have ever played. Definitely 5 stars.
